
JDG demo
========

Configuration
-------------

* Download a copy of JDG (JBoss Data Grid) server and unpack it into a dir (say JDG)
* Copy all of the files of this directory into jdg/rest: copy -r * $JDG/rest
* Copy clustered.xml into $JDG/standalone/configuration/


Starting a cluster of JDG servers
---------------------------------
* Run $JDG/bin/standalone.sh with the following arguments:

  cd $JDG/bin
  ./standalone.sh -c clustered.xml -b 192.168.1.10  -Djboss.node.name=node2

  -b points to a network interface. If multiple JDG copies should be run on
  the same host, use different logical network interfaces, e.g. using aliases

  -Djboss.node.name=NODE is used to differentiate between JDG servers. Use a
  different value for each JDG server
